dataIdInfo.idAbs:
This metadata report applies to the 2001 ADF&G Groundfish Statistical Areas. Statistical areas are polygons that divide the waters of the State of Alaska and the adjacent Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ) into small units for the purpose of reporting and analyzing fishery harvest. Each statistical area is identified by a unique 6-digit number. Groundfish statistical areas are based on a grid that measures one-half degree latitude by one degree of longitude and can be divided by lines defined in ADF&G regulations, and further subdivided based on prominent landmarks or points of land. All lines are referenced to the NAD83 datum. This revised version of the groundfish statistical areas became effective January 1, 2001. Many statistical areas were changed or subdivided to better match state and federal fishery areas. In these cases, the previous statistical area codes were retired and the revised statistical areas were assigned new numbers. If you need to compare to retired statistical areas, you will need to refer to previous versions of the groundfish statistical areas.

dataIdInfo.idPurp:
Participants in Alaska commercial fisheries are required to report the statistical area where their harvest occurs. In combination with reports on the harvest species, poundage and etc., these data are useful to analyze and visualize spatial patterns in harvest. This data set defines the current valid statistical areas that may be used on ADF&G fish tickets for groundfish. This data set should NOT be used for navigation or for determining compliance with ADF&G Commercial Fishing Regulations. Please consult the ADF&G Groundfish Commercial Fisheries Regulations for the official definitions of regulatory boundaries.
NOTE: These data attempt to depict statistical area boundaries as used for management during a specific time period. In some cases, statistical area boundaries used in practice may differ from those described in regulations, reports, maps, and other aids.

scpExt.exDesc: This data quality report applies to the commercial groundfish statistical area polygon features and associated attributes published in the PVG_Statewide_2001 feature class.

dataLineage.statement: The origin of this dataset is PVG_Statewide_1986 (originally named "ADF&G Groundfish/Shellfish Statistical Area Polygons 1986-2000"). Source data was originated by Tim Haverland (ADF&G) and published April 4, 1999.

dataSource.srcDesc: The source data for the coastline was "Alaska Coastline 1:63,360", published by the Alaska Department of Natural Resources, Land Records Section, on 02/11/1998.

prcStep.stepDesc: The original statistical area lines were converted from a shape file to an Arc/Info coverage. Then each line in this coverage was coded based on its type (e.g. coastline, 3-nautical-mile-line, statistical area grid line, land-based point-to-point statistical area line, and fixed regulatory line). (T. Haverland)

Lines were converted from NAD27 to NAD83. Some of the lines in this coverage were based on hard lines of latitude or longitude (statistical area grid lines and regulatory lines), therefore the coverage could not be converted to NAD83 as a whole. The statistical area grid lines and regulatory lines had to be separated from the other line types and defined as referenced to the NAD83 datum with no conversion. The remaining lines were converted to NAD83 using Arc/Info's PROJECT command, and all line types were appended into one coverage (gnd14ap). Then this coverage was edited to fix dangles, overshoots, missing or incorrect arcs, and other line topological errors. (T. Haverland)
prcStep.stepRat: 5 AAC 39.997 (b) The symbols °, ′, ″, indicate degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively, of longitude or latitude, based upon the North American datum of 1983.

prcStep.stepDesc: Polygon centroids were added to the line coverage gnd29ed from pvg_stat. Polygon topology was built and the coverage was edited. (T. Haverland)
prcStep.stepRat: This process was intended to fix label errors and fill in missing or incorrect statistical area codes.

prcStep.stepDesc: Polygons were split to create new statistical areas. In some cases, the new lines were digitized by the area offices and sent to ADF&G CF HQ as a MapInfo table or ArcView shape files. In others, the changes were based on coordinates in ADF&G and Federal regulations. The old statistical area numbers were retired and new numbers assigned. (T. Haverland)
prcStep.stepRat: Splits were based on requests from area and regional offices.

prcStep.stepDesc: Projected coverage to geographic and created shapefile. Merged shapefile with pvsstat1 and pvsdist1 so that shapefile contained all valid groundfish and shellfish statistical areas plus district-wide statistical areas for Southeast Alaska (these statistical areas (e.g. 010100) were used historically to record groundfish and shellfish catch when only the district was known. Added attributes to shapefile and populated using values from pvg_stat and from a spreadsheet created by G. Smith. Edited attributes. Created final shapefiles pvg_stat_2001 and pvi_stat_2001 so that each shapefile contains all current valid statistical areas for the groundfish and shellfish fisheries respectively. (T. Haverland)
Coastal statistical area polygons were clipped to the 1: 63,360 resolution shoreline published by the Alaska Department of Natural Resources (1998-02-11) (L. Hulbert and S. Larsen)
prcStep.stepRat: To improve the statewide shoreline resolution from 1: 250000 to 1:63360.

prcStep.stepDesc: Simplified the geometry of polygons. Many polygons contained multiple verteces that did not alter the overall line shape. These vertexes were individually examined, and deleted on a case by case basis. (S. Larsen)
prcStep.stepRat: To improve drawing efficiency of statewide feature classes.

prcStep.stepDesc: Attribute table structure revised, and records completed. Records for regulatory boundaries (e.g., Registration Area, District) were filled using the 2015-2016 Alaska Fish and Game Laws and Regulations (S. Larsen)
prcStep.stepRat: Many fields originated from outdated database processes/components, were confusing to end users, applied to non-groundfish fisheries only, and no longer reflect fish ticket data.

prcStep.stepDesc:
Some state waters statistical area polygons were edited to remove non-necessary waterbodies. Specific changes and authority are as follows:
395902, 385902 (approved by K. Bush 10/24/2016) 456002, 456003, 446002, 446003 (approved by C. Russ 10/25/2016) 666802, 646732, 616432, 676532, 626403, 616432, 616402, 666432 (no response as of 11/1/2016. Edits made)
prcStep.stepRat: Many state waters statistical area polygons included waterbodies that were non-suitable groundfish/shellfish habitat (i.e. rivers and wetlands), or non-existent water bodies.

prcStep.stepDesc: Updated COAR_AREA_CODE value descriptions to include the correct COAR Area Names
1. The boundaries of some statistical areas were shifted 2. Some attribute data were updated
prcStep.stepRat: 1. Some statistical area boundaries did not align with the appropriate regulatory boundaries. 2. Some statistical areas were originally assigned to the incorrect regulatory area.

prcStep.stepDesc: 1. Some metadata were updated 2. Some attributes were updated
prcStep.stepRat: The purpose of these steps were to correct errors in the original metadata and attriubte data.

prcStep.stepDesc: Attribute data for Statistical Areas 676531 and 676532 were updated. IFQ_IPHC_AREA_CODES were changed from 4D to 4E.
The fields "FISHERY_STOCK_NAME" and "FISHERY_STOCK_CODE" were added to the attribute table. Records were updated accordingly (S.Larsen).
prcStep.stepRat: These fields were added to allow data to be queried by fishery stocks in addition to regulatory "Management Areas"

prcStep.stepDesc: 1. The Start Date of statistical area 626602 was updated to 1/1/1986 (SJL 11/24/2017) 2. The Fields section of the metadata report was updated to include all entires for the FEDERAL_REPORTING_AREA_NAME (SJL 12/1/2017)

report.measDesc: The Polygon Accuracy measure is intended to ensure that statistical area polygons are accurate.
report.evalMethDesc:
Regulatory coordinates (e.g., Registration Areas, Districts, Subdistricts) were recorded from the 2015 - 2016 Alaska Fish and Game Laws and Regulations, and plotted over the groundfish statistical area feature class (PVG_Statewide_2001). Statitical area boundaries that follow regualtory boundaries were aligned to regulatory coordinates. All polygons were examined for accuracy by regional staff (Regional Supervisors, Fishery Coordinators, Biologists, Regional GIS Representatives).
Specific coordinates and regualtory authority can be found on the ADF&G Commercial Fisheries Available Statistical Area Coordinates confluence page (https://www.admin.adfg.state.ak.us/confluence/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=63897806).

ConResult.conExpl: These data were approved by S.Larsen.
